Where sustainability and style unite, you can find adidas Originals’ progressive and sustainable footwear collection in association Parley for the Oceans. Their powerful lineup, ORIGINALS by PARLEY brings to life chic consciousness, for each sneaker is made from recycled plastic waste! Slated for a nationwide launch on Earth Day, the Three Stripes and Parley bring these signature silhouettes firmly into the future. The collection will include iconic shoe franchises such as, Nizza Hi, Nizza Lo, Superstar, Stan Smith, ZX 8000, Forum Mid, Forum Low, and NMD_R1, as well as two women’s exclusives: the Forum Bold W and Nizza Platform W. Making a memorable debut at Lakmé Fashion Week through an exclusive preview on the occasion of ‘Sustainable Fashion Day,’ adidas Originals showcased the perfect blend of effortless style and innovative sustainability! So, here’s a collaboration you should keep an eye (and foot) out for!
